cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the optimal coding rate for network coding schemes, which is a fundamental problem in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on network coding schemes over a line network, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the effect of different coding schemes on the performance of the network, which is relevant to social and information networks. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a binary searching algorithm to identify the optimal coding rate, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance of different coding schemes for representative types of traffic, which is relevant to multimedia applications.
